hen, and nothing now, inbackcast, had or has for me any of the spell that enthralled my compatriots.I am not thinking of the blood spot on the darkest stone of its darkeststreet; that is hors-concours in the way of horror; I just mean that Iregarded Paris, with its gray-toned days and charcoal nights, merely as thechance setting for the most authentic and faithful joys of my life: thecolored phrase in my mind under the drizzle, the white page under the desklamp awaiting me in my humble home. <79